   <concept id="FAR_13_105" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">13.105</ph> Synopsis and posting
requirements.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d733e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d760e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> The contracting officer must comply
with the public display and synopsis requirements of <xref href="5.101.dita#FAR_5_101"
                        base="i1120993"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">5.101</xref> and <xref href="5.203.dita#FAR_5_203"
                        base="i1120755"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">5.203</xref> unless an exception
in <xref href="5.202.dita#FAR_5_202"
                        base="i1120688"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">5.202</xref> applies.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d760e24">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> When acquiring commercial products or
commercial services, or supplies or services procured in accordance
with <xref href="12.102.dita#FAR_12_102"
                        base="i1113668"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">12.102</xref>(f)(1), the contracting
officer may use a combined synopsis and solicitation. In these cases,
a separate solicitation is not required. The contracting officer
must include enough information to permit suppliers to develop quotations
or offers.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d760e32">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> See <xref href="5.102.dita#FAR_5_102"
                        base="i1121037"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">5.102</xref>(a)(6) for the requirement
to post a brand name justification or documentation required by <xref href="13.106-1.dita#FAR_13_106_1"
                        base="i1112291"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.106-1</xref>(b) or <xref href="13.501.dita#FAR_13_501"
                        base="i1111284"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.501</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d760e46">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph> When publicizing
contract actions funded in whole or in part by the American Recovery
and Reinvestment Act of 2009 (Pub. L. 111-5):</p>
               <ol id="d733e68" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d760e52">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Notices
of proposed contract actions shall follow the procedures in <xref href="5.704.dita#FAR_5_704"
                              base="i1120239"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">5.704</xref> for posting orders.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d760e60">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Award notices
shall follow the procedures in <xref href="5.705.dita#FAR_5_705"
                              base="i1120260"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">5.705</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
